hooks.prompt:
You enforce a pre-push readiness check for the agentic-sdlc codebase.

Examine the bash command in $ARGUMENTS.

Step 1: If the command does NOT contain 'git push', respond ONLY with: {}

Step 2: If it IS a git push command, respond ONLY with:
{"additionalContext": "[PRE-PUSH READINESS CHECK]\n1. DOC ACCURACY: Re-read every doc updated this session (AGENTS.md, SYSTEM_ARCHITECTURE.md, BACKLOG.md). Grep for names of changed functions/behaviors and confirm descriptions match actual implementation, not the earlier plan. Stale docs are a user-visible bug.\n2. USER CAN TEST: List what the user needs (env vars, server state, feature state). Surface any missing pieces explicitly.\n3. GAPS TO BACKLOG: Any gap, shortcut, or scale issue identified this session that does not yet have a BACKLOG.md entry must be added now. DECISIONS.md entries without a corresponding backlog item are incomplete.\n4. PRINCIPLE 8 SELF-RATING: If agents/*.ts was changed this session, enumerate: (a) which new behaviors are platform-enforced and where the enforcement code lives, (b) which are prompt-dependent and WHY platform enforcement is not possible. A prompt-dependent behavior with no justification is a delivery gap.\n5. ENFORCEMENT OUTPUT CONTRACT: If any enforcement/re-run code was added to message.ts this session, confirm it verifies PRESENCE of required output (count, format marker, structural check) — NOT absence of bad patterns (regex against output text). If a PATTERN constant or .test(capturedResponse) exists in the staged diff, this check fails — fix before pushing.\nDo all five checks before this push proceeds."}
